---
import Link from "@components/link.svelte";
import Base from "@layouts/base.astro";
import Hero from "@sections/hero.svelte";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import Socials from "@components/socials.astro";
import me from "@images/me.jpeg";
import ArrowUpRight from "~icons/lucide/arrow-up-right";
import Better from "@images/better.png";
import EmailGPT from "@images/EmailGPT.png";
import inagify from "@images/spotify.png";
---

<Base>
  <Hero>
    <Image src={me} alt="Me" class="h-full w-full object-cover" />
  </Hero>
  <main
    class="container prose prose-invert mt-32 prose-h1:font-serif
	prose-h2:font-serif prose-h3:font-serif prose-p:font-medium
	prose-a:no-underline prose-blockquote:font-serif prose-blockquote:text-2xl
	prose-blockquote:not-italic prose-em:font-serif prose-em:font-light prose-img:rounded-xl"
  >
    <h2>Who am I</h2>

    I’m a 24-year-old Software / Full Stack Engineer who enjoys turning ideas
    into real, working products. Still figuring things out—but that’s half the
    fun. I spend most of my time building, breaking, and rebuilding things on
    the web. If there’s a bug, I will find it… eventually 😄. And yes, my
    console and I have a very complicated relationship 🐛💻

    <br /><br />

    <em>Full Stack Engineer</em> • <em>Frontend Enthusiast</em> •
    <em>Open Source Contributor</em> • <em>Web3 Builder</em> • <em
      >Blockchain Curious</em
    > • <em>AI Engineer</em>

    <br /><br />

    What I’m about I like shipping things fast 🚀 ideas > perfection Turning
    “this might be cool” into “this actually works” Clean UI + smooth UX =
    non-negotiable Debugging late at night > partying (most days 😅) I Google… a
    lot (and I’m proud of it) Big fan of side projects that may or may not see
    the light of day Learning something new every week (or at least trying to)

    <br /><br />

    Current vibe Building interactive, almost-native web apps Exploring Web3 and
    blockchain beyond the hype Contributing to open source when something
    excites me Obsessing over performance, tiny details, and smooth animations

    <br /><br />

    I’m always learning, experimenting, and leveling up. If you’ve got something
    interesting to build I’m in.

